==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Panoramical
<hw>Pan`o*ram"ic*al</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of, pertaining to,
or like, a panorama; exhibiting a very broad view; <as>as, a
<ex>panoramic</ex> view</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Panoramic camera</b></col>. <cd>See under
<er>Camera</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <specif>Hence:</specif> <def>Presented with a broad
perspective; <as>as, a <ex>panoramic</ex> view of European
history</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Panorpian</ent>⟦br⟧
